Position Summary
The Credit Analyst covers a set of mainly European, US, Australian and/or Japanese financial corporate credits or REITs relevant to AXA Group’s credit investment portfolio or to AXA Group’s credit-sensitive insurance activities.
The Credit Analyst reports to Manager – Financial Corporate Credit Analysis in the Group Credit Team (“GCT”). The position is Paris based and is part of a 25 member multi-national credit team within the AXA Group holding company’s Investment & ALM department headed by the Group CIO. The AXA Group credit portfolio is in the order of EUR 190 billion with more than 3,000 issuers.

Main Responsibilities: The core duties of the Credit Analyst are:
Assessing and monitoring a portfolio of financial corporate credits and/or REITs, including eligibility proposals;
Proposing internal ratings for issuers in his/her portfolio;
Contributing to the team’s efforts to integrate ESG in credit;
Backup responsibilities on other financials/REITs sectors followed by his/her colleagues;
Liaising with Group Asset Managers and AXA local entities, as part of an AXA Group issuer eligibility process;
Collaborating closely with other GCT credit analyst and credit investment teammates;
Supporting transversal projects such as relative value and STEC adjusted performance on sectors and names covered and reduction of high yield exposure etc;
Contributing to a quantitative dashboard centralizing fundamental, market, STEC and ESG data, and other more effective and efficient approaches to credit investment and management;
Assisting Manager –Financial Corporate Credit Analysis in the preparation of the AXA Group’s Credit Universe Committee, credit process and governance documents, and regular credit-related reports
Outputs and Deliverables: The Credit Analyst’s core work results in:
Internal credit rating recommendations for all issuers in his/her portfolio;
Surveillance notes about relevant key credit events for issuers in his/her portfolio;
Credit assessments and eligibility proposals for newly proposed names;
Periodic issuer and/or sector reviews;
Follow-up of de-risking plans of one specific entity;
Qualifications
The targeted background for the Credit Analyst includes:

Master’s degree in Finance or Business from a leading university
Experience in a fundamental credit analysis role at a rating agency, financial institution, asset manager or institutional investor
Quantitative, database and modeling skills
Familiarity with credit-sensitive insurance businesses or trade finance a plus
Exposure to ESG integration in credit or ESG analysis
Fluency in written and spoken English; French a plus;
Performance Characteristics: The analyst exhibits the following in performing the role:
Strong team spirit;
Good business writing and presentation abilities in English and other languages;Emphasis on quality of analysis for internal client;
Self-motivation and a drive for constant improvement
Excellent judgment in setting priorities and meeting deadlines;
